  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Voices from the Borders (I)</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">This integration aims at promoting human rights, promoting civilian oversight and local ownership. Women and young people have been excluded from discussions on security and their priorities have often been side-lined. It is, therefore, the aim of this project to bring in viewpoints and recommendations of more effective security as well as border management from the viewpoint of women and young people.? This will be done primarily through innovative citizen diagnostic tools, such as filmmaking and mechanisms of citizen audits on basic services.?
Outcome 1: Increased capacity of women and young people to carry out a citizen diagnostic and have a voice on security priorities and other development priorities  
Outcome 2: Relationships between local authorities, women and young people are improved and local authorities take women?s and young people?s needs into account in decision-making</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">This project involves the development of two short documentary films with young women on issues of (un)employment, local governance and security perceptions to be used as an advocacy tool to raise awareness on women?s views on security. ?This approach builds on the tried and tested method of developing short-documentary films with young people in Thala, Kasserine. Those documentaries have served to change narratives and bring to the forefront the viewpoints as well as aspirations of young people in this region</narrative>
  </description>
